<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-05T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-05T15:00:00-05:00" n="979" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d979">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">883.5122/10: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-05T15:00:00-05:00">December 5, 1929—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>51. Your 73, December 3, 10 a.m.<note n="42" xml:id="d979fn42">Not
                                printed; it refers to telegram No. 70, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> Department perceives no objection to your
                            suggesting desirability of redrafting Article 2 of the Gaffir tax law in
                            the interest of clarity.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>